After winning three consecutive games at the on-going Africa Cup of Nations Cameroon 2021 , Super eagles winger Moses Simon has yet disclosed that it’s about time for Nigeria’s fourth title. Moses with scintillating performances so far in the tournament, said the Super Eagles now have the mentality and the resolve to go for the title. The Nantes of France striker insisted they would be taking their games one after the other and he further hinted journalists that the determination among the Eagles to go in the hunt for the fourth title is unbridled. He revealed that they will work towards achieving their target with practical demonstration from the training sessions before the second round game this weekend. Simon who was a second half substitute as the Super Eagles defeated Guinea Bissau 2-0 in Garoua on Wednesday’s night, noted that the Eagles cannot afford to lose focus when their objective has not been met.   Nadal relishes exciting tennis career     Qatar 2022: 1.2 million tickets sold in 24 hours     Golden Jubilee Polo Tourney: Fallen heroes honoured in Port…   - Advertisement - “Now the real work begins, and now the real competition will begin,” Simon said told NationSport. The mentality we have in the team is winning. We tried to push the opponent backward. I believe that’s why the coach called on me in the second half and I am grateful to him for the opportunity. “We all have one goal, it is not about playing. It’s all about winning the Cup. We talk to each other, everyone believe in the same objective and we are ready to make it happen. “I can’t really say how far we can go in this tournament. We just need to take things step by step,” he added. Simon also insisted that nothing has changed in his game and that he was just fortunate that things are falling in place for him in Cameroon. “For me it is normal. This is how I play so nothing has changed. cannot say but we will take it step by step,” he concluded.